Plotting method for diseasy modules

Source: R/DiseasyBaseModule.R
plot.Rd

Visualise diseasy modules.

Usage

# S3 method for class 'DiseasyBaseModule'
plot(x, ...)

Arguments

x

(Diseasy*)
The module to generate visualisation for.

...

Parameters sent to the specific plotting methods. See the $plot() method for each module

Value

NULL (called for side effects)

Examples

  immunity <- DiseasyImmunity$new()
  plot(immunity)


  immunity$set_exponential_waning(target = "hospitalisation")
#> $hospitalisation
#> function (t) 
#> exp(-t/time_scale)
#> <environment: 0x5649a8479c18>
#> attr(,"name")
#> [1] "exponential_waning"
#> attr(,"dots")
#> attr(,"dots")$time_scale
#> [1] 20
#> 
#> 
  plot(immunity)


  rm(immunity)
